@host = http://localhost:4792

### Create a user (initializes in-memory user and returns it)
POST {{host}}/user
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Partially update user — change only Name and Email
PATCH {{host}}/user
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane.doe@example.com"
}

### Partially update user — set Email to null and update Age
PATCH {{host}}/user
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": null,
  "age": 35
}

### Partially update user — update HomeAddress
PATCH {{host}}/user
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "homeAddress": {
    "street": "New Home st. 42",
    "city": "Los Angeles",
    "country": "USA",
    "postalCode": "90001"
  }
}

### Partially update user — update WorkAddresses collection
PATCH {{host}}/user
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workAddresses": [
    {
      "street": "New Office st. 100",
      "city": "San Francisco",
      "country": "USA",
      "postalCode": "94016"
    },
    {
      "street": "Remote Office st. 5",
      "city": "Austin",
      "country": "USA",
      "postalCode": "73301"
    }
  ]
}

### Empty PATCH — no changes applied, change context should be empty
PATCH {{host}}/user
Content-Type: application/json

{}
